    metaDesc: 'Is there a limit on how much money an NRI can send to India? LRS rules, repatriation limits from NRO account, and FEMA regulations explained.',
    category: 'remittance',
    readTime: 5,
    publishDate: '2025-06-05',
    content: `
<p>One of the most common questions from NRIs: "Is there a limit on how much money I can send to India?" The answer depends on the direction — sending money TO India and sending money FROM India back abroad have different rules.</p>

<h2>Sending Money TO India (No Limit)</h2>
<p>There is <strong>no upper limit on how much money an NRI can remit to India</strong> from abroad. You can send $10,000 or $10 million — as long as it comes from legitimate, tax-paid sources and you can explain the source if asked.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Funds sent to NRE account: No limit, fully repatriable back</li>
  <li>Funds sent to NRO account: No limit, but repatriation from NRO has limits</li>
  <li>Some countries (USA, EU) require banks to report transfers above $10,000 (FATF rule) — this is reporting, not a restriction</li>
</ul>

<h2>Sending Money FROM India to Abroad (NRO Repatriation)</h2>
<p>Repatriation from NRO account to abroad is limited to <strong>USD 1 million per financial year</strong> (April to March). This includes:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Rental income received in NRO account</li>
  <li>Pension received in NRO account</li>
  <li>Property sale proceeds</li>
  <li>Maturity of NRO FDs</li>
  <li>Any other Indian-source income</li>
</ul>
<p>Above USD 1 million per year requires RBI special permission.</p>

<h2>NRE Account Repatriation (No Limit)</h2>
<p>Money in NRE accounts — your foreign earnings you sent to India — can be fully repatriated at any time without any limit. This is one of the biggest advantages of maintaining NRE vs NRO accounts.</p>

<h2>Liberalised Remittance Scheme (LRS) — For Resident Indians</h2>
<p>The LRS limit of USD 250,000 per year applies to <strong>resident Indians</strong> sending money abroad, not NRIs. NRIs are NOT subject to LRS restrictions for their foreign income.</p>

<h2>Source of Funds</h2>
<p>Regardless of limits, all remittances must come from legitimate sources. Banks may request documentation for large transfers. Always maintain records of salary, business income, or other sources for amounts above $50,000.</p>

<div class="disclaimer"><p><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> FEMA regulations on NRI remittances are detailed and have exceptions. Verify current limits with RBI guidelines or a FEMA-specialist CA before large transactions.</p></div>
    `
